textBeforeTable: 2012-13 "Chat with the Mocs" Schedule The fall shows will feature head football coach Russ Huesman and focus on the football season.  The winter schedule will showcase the men's and women's basketball programs and include head coaches John Shulman and Wes Moore.  The spring show will focus on the entire UTC athletics department.  Fans will also be able to call in and ask questions about Mocs athletics.  The call in number for "Chat with the Mocs" is (423) 648-1051.  If you are not able to attend "Chat with the Mocs" tune into ESPN Radio 105.1 FM in Chattanooga.  Fans outside of the listening area can visit GoMocs.com for a live audio stream of the show.  Jefferson's is located at 618 Georgia Avenue, less than two blocks from the McKenzie Arena. "Chat with the Mocs" is an hour-long show that will broadcast live each week from Jefferson's Restaurant downtown.  Fans are encouraged to attend the show and interact with Reynolds and the Mocs, as well as take advantage of food and drink specials courtesy of Jefferson's.  Be sure to check the schedule below for specific times and dates.  The University of Tennessee at Chattanooga's 'Voice of the Mocs' Jim Reynolds hosts "Chat with the Mocs" presented by Budweiser of Chattanooga during the 2012-13 athletic season.  "Chat with the Mocs" is a live, interactive radio show that features Reynolds and
